reference_no_of_permission_being_relied_:
In December 2021, permission was granted for the following development (21/01142/FUL): 
“Refurbishment, partial demolition and extension of the existing building to provide additional office space (Use Class E(i)) and retail (Use Class E (a) or (b)) at ground floor level alongside associated cycle parking and public realm enhancements.”

In September 2022, a NMA and associated LBC was granted for the following amendments (LPA ref: 22/02501/LB and 22/02518/NMC):
1. The location and extent of the demolition of floor plates (to the interior) will be altered, this will see a net decrease in the loss of fabric by 303 sqm;
2. Sections of the replacement glazed facade will be repositioned 96mm further forward than the approved plans, to the west and north-west; and
3. The external platform passenger lift will be repositioned

In August 2023, a NMA and associated LBC was granted for the following amendments (LPA ref: 23/00248/NMC and 23/00242/LB): 
1. External metal finish: Change from anodised aluminium to powder coated aluminium;
2. Terrace upstand: Replacing concrete upstand to glazing on terrace levels with powder coated aluminium;
3. Handrails: Raise terrace metal handrails by 50mm to allow for construction tolerance and safe guarding;
4. Eastern pedestrian route landscaping: Additional staircase from Queen's Walk;
5. Main entrance door: Reduction in height and configuration;
6. Terrace Doors: Replacing sliding terrace doors with swing doors; and
7. Reinstatement of existing staircases: Existing external staircase from Queen's Walk to retail unit to be retained.
8. Amendments to Arboricultural Impact Assessment to reflect alterations included within Arboricultural Method Statement that was part approved under planning ref: 22/02611/DET.

In January 2024, a NMA and associated LBC was granted for the following amendments (LPA Ref: 23/03513/NMC and 23/03500/LB):
Changes to wording of conditions: 11, 21, 52, 53, 54 and 55
